		<!-- Start text -->
		<text>
        Follow me EV, brought to you by FGPRC.

		You can customize the displayed message on the bar through the "Follow Me EV > Select message" menu.
		You can also select a license plate in Chinese style and choose from various liveries to customize the appearance of your vehicle.
		There are several well designed and modeled interior styles to choose from. Some of them are equipped with screen display,
		so you should select 'None' for the speedometer and battery gauge.
		For more options, see "Follow Me EV > Show Options" menu.

		There are three driving mode available: Performance, Economy and Low-Power. You can switch between them in the Vehicle Options menu,
		or using buttons in some of the interiors.

		By default the simple steering mode is used. Press 'a' or 'd' to steer to a fixed angle.
		Do note that this can cause massive understeering even when driving non-aggressively.
		You can also try out the realistic steering mode in Vehicle Options menu, which may or may not help.

        Instructions for certain driving-assistance systems:
        - 'Auto Crash' system: An autopilot that keeps the vehicle on the road. It's not 100% reliable, so always monitor the road. Does not work on OSM2City roads.
		- 'Auto Speeding' system: Maintains the vehicle at a certain speed. Automatically deactivated when driver steps on either the accerlate or brake pedal.
        - Auto Hold system: Realistically implemented auto-hold system prevents unintended movement.
          It will turn itself off and enables the parking brake in certain conditions, as the real one does.
          Not avilable in some of the legacy interior style. The switch is often next to the parking brake, depending on different interior style.

        Safety system:
		- Airbags: Front and/or side airbags will be activated when crash is detected. Can be reinstalled or disabled in Vehicle Configuration menu.
		  Note that you must reinitialize the safety system to enable the airbags again once they are released.
        - AEB (Automatic Emergency Braking): Automatically brakes the vehicle to prevent crashes. Not very reliable, disabled by default.
        Note: The entire safety system will be disabled when resetting airbags. Reinitialize the system to make them work again.

        Drive safe!
		</text>
